Package words

Class SuperWord

  • java.lang.Object
    • words.Token
      • words.SuperWord
  • public class SuperWord
extends Token
    This class encodes a super word, defined as a plaintext spelling, pronunciation data, and collection of SubWords. Keeps a cache of created SuperWords to prevent duplicate WordsAPI queries.

      • getSubWords

        public java.util.ArrayList<SubWord> getSubWords​(PartOfSpeech pos,
                                                boolean inclusiveUnknown)
        Gets the collection of SubWords for a given part of speech. If @param inclusiveUnknown is true and @param pos is words.PartOfSpeech.UNKNOWN, then all SubWords are returned. If @param inclusiveUnknown is true and @param pos is not words.PartOfSpeech.UNKNOWN, then the SubWords with unknown part of speech are added to the resilts.
        Parameters:
        pos - the desired part of speech.
        inclusiveUnknown - whether or not SubWords with unknown part of speech should be included.
        Returns:
        null if the SuperWord has no SubWords of that type.

      • getFilteredSuggestions

        public java.util.ArrayList<SuperWord> getFilteredSuggestions​(PartOfSpeech thisPos,
                                                             ParameterWrappers.SuggestionPoolParameters suggestionParams,
                                                             ParameterWrappers.FilterParameters filterParams)
        Attempts to generate a collection of suggestions to substitute this word, based on the passed parameters.
        Parameters:
        thisPos - the part of speech of this word, which the suggestions should match; also used for rhmye recognition.
        suggestionParams - which suggestion pools (e.g. synonyms, parts of) to draw from, and if SubWords with unknown PoS should be included.
        filterParams - the type(s) of desired rhyme and the word(s) to rhyme with, and if syllable count should be maintained.
        Returns:
        a list of filtered suggestions, which can be empty.

      • matchesWithWrapper

        public boolean matchesWithWrapper​(ParameterWrappers.FilterParameters.RhymeType filter,
                                  SuperWord other)
        Iterates over the parts of speech of both words (worst case is full cross product evaluation) and returns true if any part of speech pairing produces a rhyme.
        Parameters:
        filter - the type of matching to perform (e.g. perfect rhyme).
        other - the word to match against.
        Returns:
        true if the two words match for any part of speech pair.

      • rhymesWithWrapper

        public boolean rhymesWithWrapper​(ParameterWrappers.FilterParameters.RhymeType filter,
                                 SuperWord other,
                                 PartOfSpeech pos1,
                                 PartOfSpeech pos2)
        Uses specific parts of speech if arguments are not null. For null PartOfSpeech arguments, iterates over all parts of speech of corresponding word.
        Parameters:
        filter - the type of matching to perform (e.g. perfect rhyme).
        other - the word to match against.
        pos1 - part of speech of this word. Can be null.
        pos2 - part of speech of the other word. Can be null.
        Returns:
        true if the words rhyme for the given parts of speech.
